 "<p>\nThe image with text iDevice can be used in a number of ways to support both\nthe emotional (affective) and learning task (cognitive) dimensions of eXe\ncontent. \n<\/p><p>\n<b>Integrating visuals with verbal summaries<\/b>\n<\/p><p>\nCognitive psychologists indicate that presenting learners with a\nrepresentative image and corresponding verbal summary (that is presented\nsimultaneously) can reduce cognitive load and enhance learning retention.\nThis iDevice can be used to present an image (photograph, diagram or\ngraphic) with a brief verbal summary covering the main points relating to\nthe image. For example, if you were teaching the functions of a four-stroke\ncombustion engine, you could have a visual for each of the four positions of\nthe piston with a brief textual summary of the key aspects of each visual.\n<\/p>": "<p>\nIDevice Obr\u00e1zek s textem lze pou\u017e\u00edt mnoha zp\u016fsoby k podpo\u0159e\nemocion\u00e1ln\u00edho (citov\u00e9ho) a v\u00fdukov\u00e9ho (pozn\u00e1vac\u00edho) rozm\u011bru eXe\nobsahu. \n<\/p><p>\n<b>Propojen\u00ed obrazov\u00e9ho a slovn\u00edho p\u0159ehledu<\/b>\n<\/p><p>\nPozn\u00e1vac\u00ed psychologie dokl\u00e1d\u00e1, \u017ee kombinace \nobrazu a odpov\u00eddaj\u00edc\u00edho textov\u00e9ho shrnut\u00ed (kter\u00e9 jsou prezentov\u00e1ny sou\u010dasn\u011b) \nm\u016f\u017ee sn\u00ed\u017eit pozn\u00e1vac\u00ed z\u00e1t\u011b\u017e student\u016f a prodlou\u017eit d\u00e9lku uchov\u00e1n\u00ed takto z\u00edskan\u00e9 informace.\nTento iDevice m\u016f\u017ee b\u00fdt pou\u017eit pro prezentov\u00e1n\u00ed obr\u00e1zk\u016f (fotografi\u00ed, diagram\u016f nebo\ngrafiky) s kr\u00e1tk\u00fdm textov\u00fdm shrnut\u00edm obsahuj\u00edc\u00ed hlavn\u00ed body vzta\u017een\u00e9\nk obr\u00e1zku. Nap\u0159\u00edklad kdy\u017e budete prob\u00edrat princip \u010dty\u0159taktn\u00edho\nspalovac\u00edho motoru, m\u016f\u017eete m\u00edt p\u0159ipraven ilustra\u010dn\u00ed obr\u00e1zek ka\u017ed\u00e9 ze \u010dty\u0159 poloh\np\u00edstu s kr\u00e1tk\u00fdm shrnut\u00edm kl\u00ed\u010dov\u00fdch aspekt\u016f z obr\u00e1zku.\n<\/p>", 
 "<p>Cloze exercises are texts or sentences where students must fill in missing words. They are often used for the following purposes:<\/p><ol><li>To check knowledge of core course concepts (this could be a pre-check, formative exercise, or summative check).<\/li><li>To check reading comprehension.<\/li><li>To check vocabulary knowledge.<\/li><li>To check word formation and\/or grammatical competence. <\/li><\/ol>": "<p>Cvi\u010den\u00ed na slov\u00ed\u010dka jsou texty nebo v\u011bty, kde mus\u00ed studenti doplnit chyb\u011bj\u00edc\u00ed slova. Jsou \u010dasto pou\u017e\u00edv\u00e1na k ov\u011b\u0159en\u00ed t\u011bchto c\u00edl\u016f:<\/p><ol><li>Znalost princip\u016f (to m\u016f\u017ee b\u00fdt formou zkou\u0161en\u00ed, tvaroslovn\u00fdch cvi\u010den\u00ed nebo souhrnnou zkou\u0161kou).<\/li><li>Porozum\u011bn\u00ed v\u00fdkladu. <\/li><li>Znalost slovn\u00ed z\u00e1soby.<\/li><li>Tvaroslovn\u00e9 a\/nebo gramatick\u00e9 dovednosti.<\/li><\/ol>", 
