 "Reflection is a teaching method often used to \nconnect theory to practice. Reflection tasks often provide learners with an \nopportunity to observe and reflect on their observations before presenting \nthese as a piece of academic work. Journals, diaries, profiles and portfolios \nare useful tools for collecting observation data. Rubrics and guides can be \neffective feedback tools.": "Reflexe je v\u00fdukov\u00e1 metoda \u010dasto pou\u017e\u00edvan\u00e1 k propojen\u00ed teorie s prax\u00ed.\nReflexe d\u00e1v\u00e1 student\u016fm mo\u017enost nahl\u00ed\u017eet a reflektovat vlastn\u00ed \u010dinnost \nd\u0159\u00edve, ne\u017e je prezentov\u00e1na jako \u010d\u00e1st akademick\u00e9 pr\u00e1ce. \nP\u0159\u00edsp\u011bvky, z\u00e1pisky, n\u00e1rysy a portfolia \njsou b\u011b\u017en\u00e9 n\u00e1stroje k z\u00edsk\u00e1v\u00e1n\u00ed pozorovan\u00fdch dat.\nRubriky a pr\u016fvodce mohou b\u00fdt efektivn\u00ed n\u00e1stroje zp\u011btn\u00e9 vazby.", 
